{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":false,"promptId":"39f1c826-35d1-4f99-bd27-915c0f3e917e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"• Findings\n\n  1. High: Data race/UB in health counters between request path and prober thread\n      - Passive updates write health state from request handling via serval-lb/handler.zig:141 -> serval-lb/strategy_core.zig:59.\n      - Active probing writes the same health state from background thread via serval-prober/scheduler.zig:43 -> serval-prober/scheduler.zig:53.\n      - HealthState counters are plain mutable arrays (failure_counts, success_counts) not atomic/locked (serval-health/health_state.zig:24, serval-health/health_state.zig:27, writes at serval-health/\n        health_state.zig:77, serval-health/health_state.zig:100).\n      - This violates enterprise safety expectations (S1/S4/C4) under concurrent load.\n  2. High: upstream.idx contract is not validated at LB init, can corrupt health mapping\n      - Selection is by array position (serval-lb/strategy_core.zig:47).\n      - Health updates use entry.upstream.idx (serval-lb/handler.zig:147).\n      - No init-time validation ensures each upstream’s idx is dense/local (0..upstreams.len-1) in serval-lb/handler.zig:73.\n      - In release builds, relying on asserts only is risky for misconfiguration (S7/C3/C5).\n  3. Medium: TLS probe misconfiguration is silent, causing permanent unhealthy state\n\n\n      - LbHandler docs say TLS probes require client_ctx when any upstream has tls=true (serval-lb/handler.zig:68), but init does not enforce it.\n      - Probe failures are swallowed as false in adapter catches (serval-prober/adapters.zig:134, serval-prober/adapters.zig:40).\n      - serval-client explicitly fails TLS connect when client_ctx == null (serval-client/client.zig:247).\n      - Result: backends may never recover, with limited observability (C4).\n  4. Medium: Prober shutdown latency can block deinit() up to full probe interval\n      - Scheduler sleeps fixed interval per cycle (serval-prober/scheduler.zig:37).\n      - deinit() sets flag then blocks on join() (serval-lb/handler.zig:120, serval-lb/handler.zig:124).\n      - With large intervals this slows graceful shutdown/drain (operability/perf concern).\n  5. Low: serval-lb README API examples are stale/inaccurate\n      - Usage example calls handler.init with old signature (serval-lb/README.md:44); current API requires client_ctx and dns_resolver (serval-lb/handler.zig:73).\n      - Struct snippet shows fields that no longer match implementation (serval-lb/README.md:57 vs actual serval-lb/handler.zig:55).\n\n  Open questions / assumptions\n\n  1. Assumed LbHandler.onLog() and prober run concurrently for the same handler instance (consistent with current thread model).\n  2. Assumed upstream.idx is expected to be local-per-pool index, not merely an opaque identifier."},"uuid":"72b22f84-c1d4-40e9-8d28-18e65164c1c6","timestamp":"2026-03-29T16:25:07.293Z","permissionMode":"default","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/nick/repos/serval","sessionId":"646a4f49-bebb-4328-acf0-8f573ea592f5","version":"2.1.86","gitBranch":"main"}
