{"parentUuid":"a94ea7b0-5102-4bed-92e2-72278370a3aa","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"39f1c826-35d1-4f99-bd27-915c0f3e917e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F98rg7FfBRUeCnb5y5XVk4","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# serval-lb\n2\t\n3\tHealth-aware load balancer handler for serval HTTP server.\n4\t\n5\t## Purpose\n6\t\n7\t**Single-pool load balancing** with integrated health tracking and automatic background probing. Backends marked unhealthy after consecutive failures recover automatically when probes succeed.\n8\t\n9\tUse `serval-lb` when you have one set of backends and need to distribute traffic across them. For routing to different backend pools based on path/host, see `serval-router`.\n10\t\n11\t## When to Use\n12\t\n13\t| Need | Module |\n14\t|------|--------|\n15\t| Balance across ONE pool of backends | **serval-lb** |\n16\t| Route to DIFFERENT pools based on path/host | serval-router |\n17\t\n18\t```\n19\tserval-lb:     client → [LB] → backend1, backend2, backend3\n20\tserval-router: client → [Router] → /api/* → pool1 → backend1, backend2\n21\t                                 → /static/* → pool2 → backend3, backend4\n22\t```\n23\t\n24\t## Exports\n25\t\n26\t- `LbHandler` - Health-aware round-robin load balancer handler (HTTP adapter)\n27\t- `LbConfig` - Configuration for thresholds, probing intervals\n28\t- `RoundRobinStrategy` - Protocol-agnostic strategy core (TCP/UDP/HTTP reuse)\n29\t- `StrategyConfig` - Strategy thresholds shared across protocol adapters\n30\t\n31\t## Usage\n32\t\n33\t```zig\n34\tconst serval_lb = @import(\"serval-lb\");\n35\tconst serval = @import(\"serval\");\n36\t\n37\tconst upstreams = [_]serval.Upstream{\n38\t    .{ .host = \"127.0.0.1\", .port = 8001, .idx = 0 },\n39\t    .{ .host = \"127.0.0.1\", .port = 8002, .idx = 1 },\n40\t    .{ .host = \"127.0.0.1\", .port = 8003, .idx = 2 },\n41\t};\n42\t\n43\tvar handler: serval_lb.LbHandler = undefined;\n44\ttry handler.init(&upstreams, .{\n45\t    .unhealthy_threshold = 3,    // 3 failures -> unhealthy\n46\t    .healthy_threshold = 2,       // 2 successes -> healthy\n47\t    .probe_interval_ms = 5000,    // Probe every 5 seconds\n48\t    .probe_timeout_ms = 2000,     // 2 second probe timeout\n49\t    .health_path = \"/health\",     // Health check endpoint\n50\t});\n51\tdefer handler.deinit();\n52\t```\n53\t\n54\t## LbHandler\n55\t\n56\t```zig\n57\tpub const LbHandler = struct {\n58\t    upstreams: []const Upstream,\n59\t    health: HealthState,\n60\t    next_idx: std.atomic.Value(u32),\n61\t    probe_running: std.atomic.Value(bool),\n62\t    probe_thread: ?std.Thread,\n63\t    lb_config: LbConfig,\n64\t\n65\t    // TigerStyle C3: Out-pointer for large struct\n66\t    pub fn init(self: *Self, upstreams: []const Upstream, lb_config: LbConfig) !void\n67\t    pub fn deinit(self: *Self) void\n68\t    pub fn selectUpstream(self: *Self, ctx: *Context, request: *const Request) Upstream\n69\t    pub fn onLog(self: *Self, ctx: *Context, entry: LogEntry) void\n70\t    pub fn countHealthy(self: *const Self) u32\n71\t    pub fn isHealthy(self: *const Self, idx: UpstreamIndex) bool\n72\t};\n73\t```\n74\t\n75\t## LbConfig\n76\t\n77\t```zig\n78\tpub const LbConfig = struct {\n79\t    unhealthy_threshold: u8 = 3,         // Consecutive failures before unhealthy\n80\t    healthy_threshold: u8 = 2,           // Consecutive successes before healthy\n81\t    enable_probing: bool = true,         // Enable background health probes\n82\t    probe_interval_ms: u32 = 5000,       // Probe cycle interval\n83\t    probe_timeout_ms: u32 = 2000,        // Per-probe timeout\n84\t    health_path: []const u8 = \"/\",       // Health check path\n85\t};\n86\t```\n87\t\n88\t## Features\n89\t\n90\t### Shared Strategy Core (HTTP/TCP/UDP)\n91\t\n92\t`strategy_core.zig` owns transport-agnostic upstream selection and health transitions.\n93\tHTTP, TCP, and UDP paths consume this core instead of embedding policy logic in\n94\ttransport mechanics.\n95\t\n96\t### Health-Aware Selection\n97\t\n98\t`selectUpstream()` skips unhealthy backends, cycling through only healthy ones:\n99\t- Uses embedded `HealthState` (atomic bitmap + threshold counters)\n100\t- Falls back to simple round-robin if all backends unhealthy (graceful degradation)\n101\t\n102\t### Passive Health Tracking\n103\t\n104\t`onLog()` hook updates health based on response status:\n105\t- 5xx responses count as failures\n106\t- Everything else counts as success\n107\t- Threshold transitions handled automatically\n108\t\n109\t### Background Health Probing\n110\t\n111\tBackground thread probes unhealthy backends for recovery (via `serval-prober`):\n112\t- HTTP GET to configured health path\n113\t- Only probes unhealthy backends (healthy ones get passive checks via traffic)\n114\t- On 2xx response, records success toward recovery threshold\n115\t\n116\t## File Structure\n117\t\n118\t```\n119\tserval-lb/\n120\t├── mod.zig            # Module exports\n121\t├── strategy_core.zig  # Protocol-agnostic round-robin + health strategy core\n122\t└── handler.zig        # HTTP adapter over strategy_core\n123\t```\n124\t\n125\t## Implementation Status\n126\t\n127\t| Feature | Status |\n128\t|---------|--------|\n129\t| Health-aware round-robin | Complete |\n130\t| Passive health tracking (onLog) | Complete |\n131\t| Background health probing | Complete |\n132\t| Weighted round-robin | Not implemented |\n133\t| Least connections | Not implemented |\n134\t| IP hash | Not implemented |\n135\t\n136\t## Dependencies\n137\t\n138\t- `serval-core` - Types, config\n139\t- `serval-health` - HealthState, UpstreamIndex\n140\t- `serval-prober` - Background health probing\n141\t\n142\t## TigerStyle Compliance\n143\t\n144\t- Out-pointer init for large struct (C3)\n145\t- ~2 assertions per function (S1)\n146\t- No runtime allocation after init (S5)\n147\t- Bounded loops over MAX_UPSTREAMS (S4)\n148\t- Explicit error logging in prober (S6)\n149\t- Explicit types: u8, u32, u64 (S2)\n150\t- Units in names: probe_interval_ms, timeout_ms (Y3)\n151\t"}]},"uuid":"99d65da4-7b72-4052-b11c-1ee8c8ce8e92","timestamp":"2026-03-29T16:25:21.038Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/nick/repos/serval/serval-lb/README.md","content":"# serval-lb\n\nHealth-aware load balancer handler for serval HTTP server.\n\n## Purpose\n\n**Single-pool load balancing** with integrated health tracking and automatic background probing. Backends marked unhealthy after consecutive failures recover automatically when probes succeed.\n\nUse `serval-lb` when you have one set of backends and need to distribute traffic across them. For routing to different backend pools based on path/host, see `serval-router`.\n\n## When to Use\n\n| Need | Module |\n|------|--------|\n| Balance across ONE pool of backends | **serval-lb** |\n| Route to DIFFERENT pools based on path/host | serval-router |\n\n```\nserval-lb:     client → [LB] → backend1, backend2, backend3\nserval-router: client → [Router] → /api/* → pool1 → backend1, backend2\n                                 → /static/* → pool2 → backend3, backend4\n```\n\n## Exports\n\n- `LbHandler` - Health-aware round-robin load balancer handler (HTTP adapter)\n- `LbConfig` - Configuration for thresholds, probing intervals\n- `RoundRobinStrategy` - Protocol-agnostic strategy core (TCP/UDP/HTTP reuse)\n- `StrategyConfig` - Strategy thresholds shared across protocol adapters\n\n## Usage\n\n```zig\nconst serval_lb = @import(\"serval-lb\");\nconst serval = @import(\"serval\");\n\nconst upstreams = [_]serval.Upstream{\n    .{ .host = \"127.0.0.1\", .port = 8001, .idx = 0 },\n    .{ .host = \"127.0.0.1\", .port = 8002, .idx = 1 },\n    .{ .host = \"127.0.0.1\", .port = 8003, .idx = 2 },\n};\n\nvar handler: serval_lb.LbHandler = undefined;\ntry handler.init(&upstreams, .{\n    .unhealthy_threshold = 3,    // 3 failures -> unhealthy\n    .healthy_threshold = 2,       // 2 successes -> healthy\n    .probe_interval_ms = 5000,    // Probe every 5 seconds\n    .probe_timeout_ms = 2000,     // 2 second probe timeout\n    .health_path = \"/health\",     // Health check endpoint\n});\ndefer handler.deinit();\n```\n\n## LbHandler\n\n```zig\npub const LbHandler = struct {\n    upstreams: []const Upstream,\n    health: HealthState,\n    next_idx: std.atomic.Value(u32),\n    probe_running: std.atomic.Value(bool),\n    probe_thread: ?std.Thread,\n    lb_config: LbConfig,\n\n    // TigerStyle C3: Out-pointer for large struct\n    pub fn init(self: *Self, upstreams: []const Upstream, lb_config: LbConfig) !void\n    pub fn deinit(self: *Self) void\n    pub fn selectUpstream(self: *Self, ctx: *Context, request: *const Request) Upstream\n    pub fn onLog(self: *Self, ctx: *Context, entry: LogEntry) void\n    pub fn countHealthy(self: *const Self) u32\n    pub fn isHealthy(self: *const Self, idx: UpstreamIndex) bool\n};\n```\n\n## LbConfig\n\n```zig\npub const LbConfig = struct {\n    unhealthy_threshold: u8 = 3,         // Consecutive failures before unhealthy\n    healthy_threshold: u8 = 2,           // Consecutive successes before healthy\n    enable_probing: bool = true,         // Enable background health probes\n    probe_interval_ms: u32 = 5000,       // Probe cycle interval\n    probe_timeout_ms: u32 = 2000,        // Per-probe timeout\n    health_path: []const u8 = \"/\",       // Health check path\n};\n```\n\n## Features\n\n### Shared Strategy Core (HTTP/TCP/UDP)\n\n`strategy_core.zig` owns transport-agnostic upstream selection and health transitions.\nHTTP, TCP, and UDP paths consume this core instead of embedding policy logic in\ntransport mechanics.\n\n### Health-Aware Selection\n\n`selectUpstream()` skips unhealthy backends, cycling through only healthy ones:\n- Uses embedded `HealthState` (atomic bitmap + threshold counters)\n- Falls back to simple round-robin if all backends unhealthy (graceful degradation)\n\n### Passive Health Tracking\n\n`onLog()` hook updates health based on response status:\n- 5xx responses count as failures\n- Everything else counts as success\n- Threshold transitions handled automatically\n\n### Background Health Probing\n\nBackground thread probes unhealthy backends for recovery (via `serval-prober`):\n- HTTP GET to configured health path\n- Only probes unhealthy backends (healthy ones get passive checks via traffic)\n- On 2xx response, records success toward recovery threshold\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\nserval-lb/\n├── mod.zig            # Module exports\n├── strategy_core.zig  # Protocol-agnostic round-robin + health strategy core\n└── handler.zig        # HTTP adapter over strategy_core\n```\n\n## Implementation Status\n\n| Feature | Status |\n|---------|--------|\n| Health-aware round-robin | Complete |\n| Passive health tracking (onLog) | Complete |\n| Background health probing | Complete |\n| Weighted round-robin | Not implemented |\n| Least connections | Not implemented |\n| IP hash | Not implemented |\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `serval-core` - Types, config\n- `serval-health` - HealthState, UpstreamIndex\n- `serval-prober` - Background health probing\n\n## TigerStyle Compliance\n\n- Out-pointer init for large struct (C3)\n- ~2 assertions per function (S1)\n- No runtime allocation after init (S5)\n- Bounded loops over MAX_UPSTREAMS (S4)\n- Explicit error logging in prober (S6)\n- Explicit types: u8, u32, u64 (S2)\n- Units in names: probe_interval_ms, timeout_ms (Y3)\n","numLines":151,"startLine":1,"totalLines":151}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"a94ea7b0-5102-4bed-92e2-72278370a3aa","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/nick/repos/serval","sessionId":"646a4f49-bebb-4328-acf0-8f573ea592f5","version":"2.1.86","gitBranch":"main","slug":"graceful-swimming-stream"}
{"parentUuid":"ee312d6b-4c6f-4bb9-aa92-0c94fd1af991","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"39f1c826-35d1-4f99-bd27-915c0f3e917e","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019VzzjfMB5Jj4KvcEq9nNGW","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t// serval-client/client.zig\n2\t//! HTTP/1.1 Client\n3\t//!\n4\t//! Unified HTTP client for making requests to upstream servers.\n5\t//! Handles DNS resolution, TCP connection, optional TLS handshake.\n6\t//! TigerStyle: Zero allocation after init, explicit errors, ~2 assertions per function.\n7\t//!\n8\t//! Layer: 2 (Infrastructure) - alongside serval-pool, serval-prober, serval-health\n9\t\n10\tconst std = @import(\"std\");\n11\tconst Io = std.Io;\n12\tconst assert = std.debug.assert;\n13\tconst posix = std.posix;\n14\t\n15\tconst serval_core = @import(\"serval-core\");\n16\tconst closeFd = serval_core.closeFd;\n17\tconst types = serval_core.types;\n18\tconst config = serval_core.config;\n19\tconst time = serval_core.time;\n20\tconst Upstream = types.Upstream;\n21\t\n22\tconst net = @import(\"serval-net\");\n23\tconst DnsResolver = net.DnsResolver;\n24\t\n25\tconst serval_socket = @import(\"serval-socket\");\n26\tconst Socket = serval_socket.Socket;\n27\tconst SocketError = serval_socket.SocketError;\n28\t\n29\tconst pool_mod = @import(\"serval-pool\");\n30\tpub const Connection = pool_mod.pool.Connection;\n31\t\n32\tconst tls = @import(\"serval-tls\");\n33\tconst ssl = tls.ssl;\n34\t\n35\tconst request_mod = @import(\"request.zig\");\n36\tconst response_mod = @import(\"response.zig\");\n37\tconst ResponseHeaders = response_mod.ResponseHeaders;\n38\tconst ResponseError = response_mod.ResponseError;\n39\t\n40\t// =============================================================================\n41\t// Error Types\n42\t// =============================================================================\n43\t\n44\t/// Unified client error type combining connection, request, and response errors.\n45\t/// TigerStyle: Explicit error set, no catch {}.\n46\tpub const ClientError = error{\n47\t    // Connection errors\n48\t    /// DNS resolution failed (hostname not found, DNS server unreachable).\n49\t    DnsResolutionFailed,\n50\t    /// TCP connection failed (refused, network unreachable).\n51\t    TcpConnectFailed,\n52\t    /// TCP connection timed out.\n53\t    TcpConnectTimeout,\n54\t    /// TLS handshake failed (certificate error, protocol mismatch).\n55\t    TlsHandshakeFailed,\n56\t\n57\t    // Send errors (from request module)\n58\t    /// Send operation failed (socket error, connection reset).\n59\t    SendFailed,\n60\t    /// Send operation timed out.\n61\t    SendTimeout,\n62\t    /// Request headers exceeded buffer size.\n63\t    BufferTooSmall,\n64\t\n65\t    // Receive errors (from response module)\n66\t    /// Receive operation failed (socket error).\n67\t    RecvFailed,\n68\t    /// Receive operation timed out.\n69\t    RecvTimeout,\n70\t    /// Response headers exceeded buffer size.\n71\t    ResponseHeadersTooLarge,\n72\t    /// Invalid HTTP status line.\n73\t    InvalidResponseStatus,\n74\t    /// Invalid HTTP response headers.\n75\t    InvalidResponseHeaders,\n76\t    /// Connection closed by peer before response complete.\n77\t    ConnectionClosed,\n78\t};\n79\t\n80\t// =============================================================================\n81\t// Result Types\n82\t// =============================================================================\n83\t\n84\t/// Result of connecting to an upstream server.\n85\t/// Includes timing information for observability.\n86\t/// TigerStyle: Explicit struct with timing fields.\n87\tpub const ConnectResult = struct {\n88\t    /// Connection to upstream (caller must release to pool or close).\n89\t    conn: Connection,\n90\t    /// Duration of DNS resolution in nanoseconds (0 if cached or IP address).\n91\t    dns_duration_ns: u64,\n92\t    /// Duration of TCP connect in nanoseconds.\n93\t    tcp_connect_duration_ns: u64,\n94\t    /// Duration of TLS handshake in nanoseconds (0 if plaintext).\n95\t    tls_handshake_duration_ns: u64,\n96\t    /// Local port of the connection.\n97\t    local_port: u16,\n98\t    /// Whether requested connect timeout semantics were honored by IO backend.\n99\t    connect_timeout_honored: bool,\n100\t};\n101\t\n102\tconst TcpConnectResult = struct {\n103\t    fd: i32,\n104\t    timeout_honored: bool,\n105\t};\n106\t\n107\t/// Result of a complete HTTP request (connect + send + read headers).\n108\t/// TigerStyle: Explicit struct with owned connection.\n109\tpub const RequestResult = struct {\n110\t    /// Connection to upstream (caller must release to pool or close).\n111\t    conn: Connection,\n112\t    /// Parsed response headers.\n113\t    response: ResponseHeaders,\n114\t};\n115\t\n116\t// =============================================================================\n117\t// Client\n118\t// =============================================================================\n119\t\n120\t/// HTTP/1.1 client for upstream connections.\n121\t/// TigerStyle: Fixed configuration, no runtime allocation.\n122\tpub const Client = struct {\n123\t    /// Allocator for potential future use (currently unused).\n124\t    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n125\t\n126\t    /// DNS resolver for hostname lookups.\n127\t    dns_resolver: *DnsResolver,\n128\t\n129\t    /// TLS context for client connections (null = plaintext only).\n130\t    /// TigerStyle: Optional TLS support, explicit null for plaintext.\n131\t    client_ctx: ?*ssl.SSL_CTX,\n132\t\n133\t    /// Whether to verify upstream TLS certificates.\n134\t    /// TigerStyle: Explicit boolean, no implicit behavior.\n135\t    verify_tls: bool,\n136\t\n137\t    /// Whether to enable kernel TLS offload for connections.\n138\t    /// Default true for performance. Set false if kTLS causes EBADMSG errors\n139\t    /// with specific servers (e.g., K8s API).\n140\t    enable_ktls: bool,\n141\t\n142\t    /// Initialize a new HTTP client with kTLS enabled (default).\n143\t    /// TigerStyle S1: Assertions for preconditions.\n144\t    pub fn init(\n145\t        allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n146\t        dns_resolver: *DnsResolver,\n147\t        client_ctx: ?*ssl.SSL_CTX,\n148\t        verify_tls: bool,\n149\t    ) Client {\n150\t        return initWithOptions(allocator, dns_resolver, client_ctx, verify_tls, true);\n151\t    }\n152\t\n153\t    /// Initialize a new HTTP client with explicit kTLS control.\n154\t    /// TigerStyle S1: Assertions for preconditions.\n155\t    pub fn initWithOptions(\n156\t        allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n157\t        dns_resolver: *DnsResolver,\n158\t        client_ctx: ?*ssl.SSL_CTX,\n159\t        verify_tls: bool,\n160\t        enable_ktls: bool,\n161\t    ) Client {\n162\t        // S1: precondition - dns_resolver must be valid\n163\t        assert(@intFromPtr(dns_resolver) != 0);\n164\t        // S1: precondition - if verify_tls is true, client_ctx should be set (advisory)\n165\t        // Note: We don't assert this because plaintext-only clients may have verify_tls=true\n166\t        // as a default, and client_ctx=null means TLS upstreams will fail explicitly.\n167\t\n168\t        return .{\n169\t            .allocator = allocator,\n170\t            .dns_resolver = dns_resolver,\n171\t            .client_ctx = client_ctx,\n172\t            .verify_tls = verify_tls,\n173\t            .enable_ktls = enable_ktls,\n174\t        };\n175\t    }\n176\t\n177\t    /// Deinitialize the client.\n178\t    /// Currently a no-op since we don't own the dns_resolver or client_ctx.\n179\t    /// TigerStyle: Explicit cleanup path, even if empty.\n180\t    pub fn deinit(self: *Client) void {\n181\t        // We don't own dns_resolver or client_ctx, so nothing to clean up\n182\t        _ = self;\n183\t    }\n184\t\n185\t    /// Connect to an upstream server.\n186\t    /// Performs DNS resolution, TCP connection, and optional TLS handshake.\n187\t    /// Returns ConnectResult with timing information for observability.\n188\t    /// TigerStyle S1: ~2 assertions, S3: bounded operations via Io.\n189\t    pub fn connect(\n190\t        self: *Client,\n191\t        upstream: Upstream,\n192\t        io: Io,\n193\t    ) ClientError!ConnectResult {\n194\t        return self.connectWithTimeout(upstream, io, .none);\n195\t    }\n196\t\n197\t    /// Connect to an upstream server with explicit TCP connect timeout.\n198\t    /// TigerStyle S1: ~2 assertions, S3: bounded operations via Io timeout.\n199\t    pub fn connectWithTimeout(\n200\t        self: *Client,\n201\t        upstream: Upstream,\n202\t        io: Io,\n203\t        connect_timeout: Io.Timeout,\n204\t    ) ClientError!ConnectResult {\n205\t        // S1: preconditions\n206\t        assert(upstream.host.len > 0); // S1: non-empty host\n207\t        assert(upstream.port > 0); // S1: valid port\n208\t\n209\t        // Step 1: DNS resolution (timed)\n210\t        const dns_start_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n211\t        const resolve_result = self.dns_resolver.resolve(\n212\t            upstream.host,\n213\t            upstream.port,\n214\t            io,\n215\t        ) catch {\n216\t            return ClientError.DnsResolutionFailed;\n217\t        };\n218\t        const dns_end_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n219\t        const dns_duration_ns = time.elapsedNanos(dns_start_ns, dns_end_ns);\n220\t\n221\t        // S2: postcondition - resolved address has correct port\n222\t        assert(resolve_result.address.getPort() == upstream.port);\n223\t\n224\t        // Step 2: TCP connection (timed)\n225\t        const tcp_start_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n226\t        const tcp_result = tcpConnect(resolve_result.address, io, connect_timeout) catch |err| {\n227\t            return mapConnectError(err);\n228\t        };\n229\t        const fd = tcp_result.fd;\n230\t        const tcp_end_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n231\t        const tcp_connect_duration_ns = time.elapsedNanos(tcp_start_ns, tcp_end_ns);\n232\t\n233\t        // S2: postcondition - valid fd\n234\t        assert(fd >= 0);\n235\t\n236\t        // Configure socket for low latency\n237\t        _ = net.set_tcp_no_delay(fd);\n238\t        _ = net.set_tcp_keep_alive(fd, 60, 10, 3);\n239\t\n240\t        // Get local port for observability\n241\t        const local_port = getLocalPort(fd);\n242\t\n243\t        // Step 3: Optional TLS handshake (timed)\n244\t        const tls_start_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n245\t        const socket: Socket = if (upstream.tls) blk: {\n246\t            // TLS required - client_ctx must be set\n247\t            const ctx = self.client_ctx orelse {\n248\t                // No TLS context - cannot connect to TLS upstream\n249\t                closeFd(fd);\n250\t                return ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed;\n251\t            };\n252\t\n253\t            // Perform TLS handshake with SNI\n254\t            // Strip trailing dot from hostname for SNI (FQDN dots are not valid in SNI)\n255\t            const sni_host = if (std.mem.endsWith(u8, upstream.host, \".\"))\n256\t                upstream.host[0 .. upstream.host.len - 1]\n257\t            else\n258\t                upstream.host;\n259\t\n260\t            const desired_alpn: ?[]const u8 = switch (upstream.http_protocol) {\n261\t                .h1 => \"http/1.1\",\n262\t                .h2 => \"h2\",\n263\t                .h2c => null,\n264\t            };\n265\t\n266\t            var tls_socket = Socket.TLS.TLSSocket.init_client(\n267\t                fd,\n268\t                ctx,\n269\t                sni_host,\n270\t                self.enable_ktls,\n271\t                desired_alpn,\n272\t                self.verify_tls,\n273\t            ) catch {\n274\t                closeFd(fd);\n275\t                return ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed;\n276\t            };\n277\t\n278\t            if (upstream.http_protocol == .h2) {\n279\t                const negotiated = switch (tls_socket) {\n280\t                    .tls => |tls_conn| tls_conn.stream.info.alpn(),\n281\t                    .plain => null,\n282\t                } orelse {\n283\t                    tls_socket.close();\n284\t                    return ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed;\n285\t                };\n286\t                if (!std.mem.eql(u8, negotiated, \"h2\")) {\n287\t                    tls_socket.close();\n288\t                    return ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed;\n289\t                }\n290\t            }\n291\t\n292\t            break :blk tls_socket;\n293\t        } else blk: {\n294\t            // Plaintext connection\n295\t            break :blk Socket.Plain.init_client(fd);\n296\t        };\n297\t        const tls_end_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n298\t        const tls_handshake_duration_ns = if (upstream.tls)\n299\t            time.elapsedNanos(tls_start_ns, tls_end_ns)\n300\t        else\n301\t            0;\n302\t\n303\t        // Build connection with timestamps\n304\t        const now_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n305\t        const conn = Connection{\n306\t            .socket = socket,\n307\t            .created_ns = now_ns,\n308\t            .last_used_ns = now_ns,\n309\t        };\n310\t\n311\t        return ConnectResult{\n312\t            .conn = conn,\n313\t            .dns_duration_ns = dns_duration_ns,\n314\t            .tcp_connect_duration_ns = tcp_connect_duration_ns,\n315\t            .tls_handshake_duration_ns = tls_handshake_duration_ns,\n316\t            .local_port = local_port,\n317\t            .connect_timeout_honored = tcp_result.timeout_honored,\n318\t        };\n319\t    }\n320\t\n321\t    /// Send an HTTP request on an existing connection.\n322\t    /// Delegates to request.sendRequest with proper error mapping.\n323\t    /// TigerStyle S1: Precondition assertions.\n324\t    pub fn sendRequest(\n325\t        self: *Client,\n326\t        conn: *Connection,\n327\t        req: *const types.Request,\n328\t        effective_path: ?[]const u8,\n329\t    ) ClientError!void {\n330\t        _ = self; // Client state not needed for send\n331\t\n332\t        // S1: preconditions\n333\t        const path = effective_path orelse req.path;\n334\t        assert(path.len > 0); // S1: non-empty path\n335\t\n336\t        request_mod.sendRequest(&conn.socket, req, effective_path) catch |err| {\n337\t            return mapRequestError(err);\n338\t        };\n339\t    }\n340\t\n341\t    /// Read HTTP response headers from an existing connection.\n342\t    /// Delegates to response.readResponseHeaders with proper error mapping.\n343\t    /// TigerStyle S1: Precondition assertions.\n344\t    pub fn readResponseHeaders(\n345\t        self: *Client,\n346\t        conn: *Connection,\n347\t        header_buf: []u8,\n348\t    ) ClientError!ResponseHeaders {\n349\t        _ = self; // Client state not needed for receive\n350\t\n351\t        // S1: preconditions\n352\t        assert(header_buf.len > 0); // S1: non-empty buffer\n353\t        assert(header_buf.len <= config.MAX_HEADER_SIZE_BYTES); // S1: bounded buffer\n354\t\n355\t        return response_mod.readResponseHeaders(&conn.socket, header_buf) catch |err| {\n356\t            return mapResponseError(err);\n357\t        };\n358\t    }\n359\t\n360\t    /// Perform a complete HTTP request (connect + send + read headers).\n361\t    /// Convenience function for simple request/response flows.\n362\t    /// TigerStyle S1: Precondition assertions.\n363\t    pub fn request(\n364\t        self: *Client,\n365\t        upstream: Upstream,\n366\t        req: *const types.Request,\n367\t        header_buf: []u8,\n368\t        io: Io,\n369\t    ) ClientError!RequestResult {\n370\t        // S1: preconditions\n371\t        assert(upstream.host.len > 0); // S1: non-empty host\n372\t        assert(header_buf.len > 0); // S1: non-empty buffer\n373\t\n374\t        // Step 1: Connect\n375\t        var connect_result = try self.connect(upstream, io);\n376\t        errdefer connect_result.conn.close();\n377\t\n378\t        // Step 2: Send request\n379\t        try self.sendRequest(&connect_result.conn, req, null);\n380\t\n381\t        // Step 3: Read response headers\n382\t        const response = try self.readResponseHeaders(&connect_result.conn, header_buf);\n383\t\n384\t        // S2: postcondition - valid response status\n385\t        assert(response.status >= 100 and response.status <= 599);\n386\t\n387\t        return .{\n388\t            .conn = connect_result.conn,\n389\t            .response = response,\n390\t        };\n391\t    }\n392\t};\n393\t\n394\t// =============================================================================\n395\t// Internal Functions\n396\t// =============================================================================\n397\t\n398\t/// Get local port from connected socket.\n399\t/// Returns 0 if unable to retrieve (non-fatal).\n400\t/// TigerStyle: Graceful fallback, no panic on failure.\n401\tfn getLocalPort(fd: i32) u16 {\n402\t    assert(fd >= 0);\n403\t\n404\t    var addr: posix.sockaddr.in = std.mem.zeroes(posix.sockaddr.in);\n405\t    var addr_len: posix.socklen_t = @sizeOf(posix.sockaddr.in);\n406\t\n407\t    if (std.c.getsockname(fd, @ptrCast(&addr), &addr_len) != 0) {\n408\t        return 0;\n409\t    }\n410\t\n411\t    return std.mem.bigToNative(u16, addr.port);\n412\t}\n413\t\n414\t/// Perform TCP connection using Io async API.\n415\t/// TigerStyle: Bounded via Io cancellation, explicit error return.\n416\tfn tcpConnect(address: Io.net.IpAddress, io: Io, connect_timeout: Io.Timeout) !TcpConnectResult {\n417\t    // Use IpAddress.connect() to perform async TCP connect\n418\t    // This creates the socket and connects in one step.\n419\t    const stream = address.connect(io, .{\n420\t        .mode = .stream,\n421\t        .timeout = connect_timeout,\n422\t    }) catch |err| {\n423\t        if (err == error.OptionUnsupported and connect_timeout != .none) {\n424\t            // Some IO backends (notably uring today) do not yet support\n425\t            // connect-time timeout options. Fall back to backend-default connect\n426\t            // semantics so callers can still establish connections.\n427\t            const fallback = address.connect(io, .{\n428\t                .mode = .stream,\n429\t                .timeout = .none,\n430\t            }) catch |fallback_err| {\n431\t                return fallback_err;\n432\t            };\n433\t            return .{\n434\t                .fd = fallback.socket.handle,\n435\t                .timeout_honored = false,\n436\t            };\n437\t        }\n438\t        return err;\n439\t    };\n440\t\n441\t    return .{\n442\t        .fd = stream.socket.handle,\n443\t        .timeout_honored = true,\n444\t    };\n445\t}\n446\t\n447\t/// Map TCP connect errors to ClientError.\n448\t/// TigerStyle S6: Explicit error handling.\n449\tfn mapConnectError(err: anyerror) ClientError {\n450\t    return switch (err) {\n451\t        error.ConnectionRefused => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n452\t        error.NetworkUnreachable => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n453\t        error.ConnectionFailed => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n454\t        error.ConnectionTimedOut, error.Timeout => ClientError.TcpConnectTimeout,\n455\t        error.ConnectionResetByPeer => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n456\t        else => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n457\t    };\n458\t}\n459\t\n460\t/// Map request module errors to ClientError.\n461\t/// TigerStyle S6: Explicit error handling.\n462\tfn mapRequestError(err: request_mod.ClientError) ClientError {\n463\t    return switch (err) {\n464\t        request_mod.ClientError.SendFailed => ClientError.SendFailed,\n465\t        request_mod.ClientError.SendTimeout => ClientError.SendTimeout,\n466\t        request_mod.ClientError.BufferTooSmall => ClientError.BufferTooSmall,\n467\t    };\n468\t}\n469\t\n470\t/// Map response module errors to ClientError.\n471\t/// TigerStyle S6: Explicit error handling.\n472\tfn mapResponseError(err: ResponseError) ClientError {\n473\t    return switch (err) {\n474\t        ResponseError.RecvFailed => ClientError.RecvFailed,\n475\t        ResponseError.RecvTimeout => ClientError.RecvTimeout,\n476\t        ResponseError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge => ClientError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge,\n477\t        ResponseError.InvalidResponseStatus => ClientError.InvalidResponseStatus,\n478\t        ResponseError.InvalidResponseHeaders => ClientError.InvalidResponseHeaders,\n479\t        ResponseError.ConnectionClosed => ClientError.ConnectionClosed,\n480\t    };\n481\t}\n482\t\n483\t// =============================================================================\n484\t// Tests\n485\t// =============================================================================\n486\t\n487\ttest \"Client.init creates client with valid fields\" {\n488\t    var dns_resolver: DnsResolver = undefined;\n489\t    DnsResolver.init(&dns_resolver, .{});\n490\t    const client = Client.init(\n491\t        std.testing.allocator,\n492\t        &dns_resolver,\n493\t        null, // No TLS\n494\t        false,\n495\t    );\n496\t\n497\t    try std.testing.expect(@intFromPtr(client.dns_resolver) != 0);\n498\t    try std.testing.expect(client.client_ctx == null);\n499\t    try std.testing.expect(client.verify_tls == false);\n500\t}\n501\t\n502\ttest \"Client.init with TLS context\" {\n503\t    var dns_resolver: DnsResolver = undefined;\n504\t    DnsResolver.init(&dns_resolver, .{});\n505\t\n506\t    // We can't actually create a valid SSL_CTX in tests without OpenSSL setup,\n507\t    // but we can verify the field is stored correctly with a dummy pointer.\n508\t    // In real usage, the caller provides a properly initialized SSL_CTX.\n509\t    const client = Client.init(\n510\t        std.testing.allocator,\n511\t        &dns_resolver,\n512\t        null, // No TLS in test\n513\t        true, // verify_tls enabled\n514\t    );\n515\t\n516\t    try std.testing.expect(client.verify_tls == true);\n517\t}\n518\t\n519\ttest \"Client.deinit is safe to call\" {\n520\t    var dns_resolver: DnsResolver = undefined;\n521\t    DnsResolver.init(&dns_resolver, .{});\n522\t    var client = Client.init(\n523\t        std.testing.allocator,\n524\t        &dns_resolver,\n525\t        null,\n526\t        false,\n527\t    );\n528\t\n529\t    // Should not crash\n530\t    client.deinit();\n531\t}\n532\t\n533\ttest \"ClientError error set has all expected variants\" {\n534\t    // Verify all error variants exist\n535\t    const errors = [_]ClientError{\n536\t        ClientError.DnsResolutionFailed,\n537\t        ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n538\t        ClientError.TcpConnectTimeout,\n539\t        ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed,\n540\t        ClientError.SendFailed,\n541\t        ClientError.SendTimeout,\n542\t        ClientError.BufferTooSmall,\n543\t        ClientError.RecvFailed,\n544\t        ClientError.RecvTimeout,\n545\t        ClientError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge,\n546\t        ClientError.InvalidResponseStatus,\n547\t        ClientError.InvalidResponseHeaders,\n548\t        ClientError.ConnectionClosed,\n549\t    };\n550\t\n551\t    // Each error should be distinct\n552\t    for (errors, 0..) |err1, i| {\n553\t        for (errors[i + 1 ..]) |err2| {\n554\t            try std.testing.expect(err1 != err2);\n555\t        }\n556\t    }\n557\t}\n558\t\n559\ttest \"RequestResult struct layout\" {\n560\t    // Verify struct has expected fields\n561\t    const info = @typeInfo(RequestResult);\n562\t    try std.testing.expect(info == .@\"struct\");\n563\t\n564\t    const fields = info.@\"struct\".fields;\n565\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(usize, 2), fields.len);\n566\t    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"conn\", fields[0].name);\n567\t    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"response\", fields[1].name);\n568\t}\n569\t\n570\ttest \"mapRequestError maps all variants\" {\n571\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.SendFailed, mapRequestError(request_mod.ClientError.SendFailed));\n572\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.SendTimeout, mapRequestError(request_mod.ClientError.SendTimeout));\n573\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.BufferTooSmall, mapRequestError(request_mod.ClientError.BufferTooSmall));\n574\t}\n575\t\n576\ttest \"mapResponseError maps all variants\" {\n577\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.RecvFailed, mapResponseError(ResponseError.RecvFailed));\n578\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.RecvTimeout, mapResponseError(ResponseError.RecvTimeout));\n579\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge, mapResponseError(ResponseError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge));\n580\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.InvalidResponseStatus, mapResponseError(ResponseError.InvalidResponseStatus));\n581\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.InvalidResponseHeaders, mapResponseError(ResponseError.InvalidResponseHeaders));\n582\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.ConnectionClosed, mapResponseError(ResponseError.ConnectionClosed));\n583\t}\n584\t\n585\ttest \"mapConnectError maps common errors\" {\n586\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.ConnectionRefused));\n587\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.NetworkUnreachable));\n588\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.ConnectionFailed));\n589\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectTimeout, mapConnectError(error.ConnectionTimedOut));\n590\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectTimeout, mapConnectError(error.Timeout));\n591\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.ConnectionResetByPeer));\n592\t    // Unknown errors map to TcpConnectFailed\n593\t    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.OutOfMemory));\n594\t}\n595\t"}]},"uuid":"e34a73ab-22ee-4b93-9c69-0f58ad40ddd4","timestamp":"2026-03-29T16:25:21.168Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/nick/repos/serval/serval-client/client.zig","content":"// serval-client/client.zig\n//! HTTP/1.1 Client\n//!\n//! Unified HTTP client for making requests to upstream servers.\n//! Handles DNS resolution, TCP connection, optional TLS handshake.\n//! TigerStyle: Zero allocation after init, explicit errors, ~2 assertions per function.\n//!\n//! Layer: 2 (Infrastructure) - alongside serval-pool, serval-prober, serval-health\n\nconst std = @import(\"std\");\nconst Io = std.Io;\nconst assert = std.debug.assert;\nconst posix = std.posix;\n\nconst serval_core = @import(\"serval-core\");\nconst closeFd = serval_core.closeFd;\nconst types = serval_core.types;\nconst config = serval_core.config;\nconst time = serval_core.time;\nconst Upstream = types.Upstream;\n\nconst net = @import(\"serval-net\");\nconst DnsResolver = net.DnsResolver;\n\nconst serval_socket = @import(\"serval-socket\");\nconst Socket = serval_socket.Socket;\nconst SocketError = serval_socket.SocketError;\n\nconst pool_mod = @import(\"serval-pool\");\npub const Connection = pool_mod.pool.Connection;\n\nconst tls = @import(\"serval-tls\");\nconst ssl = tls.ssl;\n\nconst request_mod = @import(\"request.zig\");\nconst response_mod = @import(\"response.zig\");\nconst ResponseHeaders = response_mod.ResponseHeaders;\nconst ResponseError = response_mod.ResponseError;\n\n// =============================================================================\n// Error Types\n// =============================================================================\n\n/// Unified client error type combining connection, request, and response errors.\n/// TigerStyle: Explicit error set, no catch {}.\npub const ClientError = error{\n    // Connection errors\n    /// DNS resolution failed (hostname not found, DNS server unreachable).\n    DnsResolutionFailed,\n    /// TCP connection failed (refused, network unreachable).\n    TcpConnectFailed,\n    /// TCP connection timed out.\n    TcpConnectTimeout,\n    /// TLS handshake failed (certificate error, protocol mismatch).\n    TlsHandshakeFailed,\n\n    // Send errors (from request module)\n    /// Send operation failed (socket error, connection reset).\n    SendFailed,\n    /// Send operation timed out.\n    SendTimeout,\n    /// Request headers exceeded buffer size.\n    BufferTooSmall,\n\n    // Receive errors (from response module)\n    /// Receive operation failed (socket error).\n    RecvFailed,\n    /// Receive operation timed out.\n    RecvTimeout,\n    /// Response headers exceeded buffer size.\n    ResponseHeadersTooLarge,\n    /// Invalid HTTP status line.\n    InvalidResponseStatus,\n    /// Invalid HTTP response headers.\n    InvalidResponseHeaders,\n    /// Connection closed by peer before response complete.\n    ConnectionClosed,\n};\n\n// =============================================================================\n// Result Types\n// =============================================================================\n\n/// Result of connecting to an upstream server.\n/// Includes timing information for observability.\n/// TigerStyle: Explicit struct with timing fields.\npub const ConnectResult = struct {\n    /// Connection to upstream (caller must release to pool or close).\n    conn: Connection,\n    /// Duration of DNS resolution in nanoseconds (0 if cached or IP address).\n    dns_duration_ns: u64,\n    /// Duration of TCP connect in nanoseconds.\n    tcp_connect_duration_ns: u64,\n    /// Duration of TLS handshake in nanoseconds (0 if plaintext).\n    tls_handshake_duration_ns: u64,\n    /// Local port of the connection.\n    local_port: u16,\n    /// Whether requested connect timeout semantics were honored by IO backend.\n    connect_timeout_honored: bool,\n};\n\nconst TcpConnectResult = struct {\n    fd: i32,\n    timeout_honored: bool,\n};\n\n/// Result of a complete HTTP request (connect + send + read headers).\n/// TigerStyle: Explicit struct with owned connection.\npub const RequestResult = struct {\n    /// Connection to upstream (caller must release to pool or close).\n    conn: Connection,\n    /// Parsed response headers.\n    response: ResponseHeaders,\n};\n\n// =============================================================================\n// Client\n// =============================================================================\n\n/// HTTP/1.1 client for upstream connections.\n/// TigerStyle: Fixed configuration, no runtime allocation.\npub const Client = struct {\n    /// Allocator for potential future use (currently unused).\n    allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n\n    /// DNS resolver for hostname lookups.\n    dns_resolver: *DnsResolver,\n\n    /// TLS context for client connections (null = plaintext only).\n    /// TigerStyle: Optional TLS support, explicit null for plaintext.\n    client_ctx: ?*ssl.SSL_CTX,\n\n    /// Whether to verify upstream TLS certificates.\n    /// TigerStyle: Explicit boolean, no implicit behavior.\n    verify_tls: bool,\n\n    /// Whether to enable kernel TLS offload for connections.\n    /// Default true for performance. Set false if kTLS causes EBADMSG errors\n    /// with specific servers (e.g., K8s API).\n    enable_ktls: bool,\n\n    /// Initialize a new HTTP client with kTLS enabled (default).\n    /// TigerStyle S1: Assertions for preconditions.\n    pub fn init(\n        allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n        dns_resolver: *DnsResolver,\n        client_ctx: ?*ssl.SSL_CTX,\n        verify_tls: bool,\n    ) Client {\n        return initWithOptions(allocator, dns_resolver, client_ctx, verify_tls, true);\n    }\n\n    /// Initialize a new HTTP client with explicit kTLS control.\n    /// TigerStyle S1: Assertions for preconditions.\n    pub fn initWithOptions(\n        allocator: std.mem.Allocator,\n        dns_resolver: *DnsResolver,\n        client_ctx: ?*ssl.SSL_CTX,\n        verify_tls: bool,\n        enable_ktls: bool,\n    ) Client {\n        // S1: precondition - dns_resolver must be valid\n        assert(@intFromPtr(dns_resolver) != 0);\n        // S1: precondition - if verify_tls is true, client_ctx should be set (advisory)\n        // Note: We don't assert this because plaintext-only clients may have verify_tls=true\n        // as a default, and client_ctx=null means TLS upstreams will fail explicitly.\n\n        return .{\n            .allocator = allocator,\n            .dns_resolver = dns_resolver,\n            .client_ctx = client_ctx,\n            .verify_tls = verify_tls,\n            .enable_ktls = enable_ktls,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Deinitialize the client.\n    /// Currently a no-op since we don't own the dns_resolver or client_ctx.\n    /// TigerStyle: Explicit cleanup path, even if empty.\n    pub fn deinit(self: *Client) void {\n        // We don't own dns_resolver or client_ctx, so nothing to clean up\n        _ = self;\n    }\n\n    /// Connect to an upstream server.\n    /// Performs DNS resolution, TCP connection, and optional TLS handshake.\n    /// Returns ConnectResult with timing information for observability.\n    /// TigerStyle S1: ~2 assertions, S3: bounded operations via Io.\n    pub fn connect(\n        self: *Client,\n        upstream: Upstream,\n        io: Io,\n    ) ClientError!ConnectResult {\n        return self.connectWithTimeout(upstream, io, .none);\n    }\n\n    /// Connect to an upstream server with explicit TCP connect timeout.\n    /// TigerStyle S1: ~2 assertions, S3: bounded operations via Io timeout.\n    pub fn connectWithTimeout(\n        self: *Client,\n        upstream: Upstream,\n        io: Io,\n        connect_timeout: Io.Timeout,\n    ) ClientError!ConnectResult {\n        // S1: preconditions\n        assert(upstream.host.len > 0); // S1: non-empty host\n        assert(upstream.port > 0); // S1: valid port\n\n        // Step 1: DNS resolution (timed)\n        const dns_start_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n        const resolve_result = self.dns_resolver.resolve(\n            upstream.host,\n            upstream.port,\n            io,\n        ) catch {\n            return ClientError.DnsResolutionFailed;\n        };\n        const dns_end_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n        const dns_duration_ns = time.elapsedNanos(dns_start_ns, dns_end_ns);\n\n        // S2: postcondition - resolved address has correct port\n        assert(resolve_result.address.getPort() == upstream.port);\n\n        // Step 2: TCP connection (timed)\n        const tcp_start_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n        const tcp_result = tcpConnect(resolve_result.address, io, connect_timeout) catch |err| {\n            return mapConnectError(err);\n        };\n        const fd = tcp_result.fd;\n        const tcp_end_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n        const tcp_connect_duration_ns = time.elapsedNanos(tcp_start_ns, tcp_end_ns);\n\n        // S2: postcondition - valid fd\n        assert(fd >= 0);\n\n        // Configure socket for low latency\n        _ = net.set_tcp_no_delay(fd);\n        _ = net.set_tcp_keep_alive(fd, 60, 10, 3);\n\n        // Get local port for observability\n        const local_port = getLocalPort(fd);\n\n        // Step 3: Optional TLS handshake (timed)\n        const tls_start_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n        const socket: Socket = if (upstream.tls) blk: {\n            // TLS required - client_ctx must be set\n            const ctx = self.client_ctx orelse {\n                // No TLS context - cannot connect to TLS upstream\n                closeFd(fd);\n                return ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed;\n            };\n\n            // Perform TLS handshake with SNI\n            // Strip trailing dot from hostname for SNI (FQDN dots are not valid in SNI)\n            const sni_host = if (std.mem.endsWith(u8, upstream.host, \".\"))\n                upstream.host[0 .. upstream.host.len - 1]\n            else\n                upstream.host;\n\n            const desired_alpn: ?[]const u8 = switch (upstream.http_protocol) {\n                .h1 => \"http/1.1\",\n                .h2 => \"h2\",\n                .h2c => null,\n            };\n\n            var tls_socket = Socket.TLS.TLSSocket.init_client(\n                fd,\n                ctx,\n                sni_host,\n                self.enable_ktls,\n                desired_alpn,\n                self.verify_tls,\n            ) catch {\n                closeFd(fd);\n                return ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed;\n            };\n\n            if (upstream.http_protocol == .h2) {\n                const negotiated = switch (tls_socket) {\n                    .tls => |tls_conn| tls_conn.stream.info.alpn(),\n                    .plain => null,\n                } orelse {\n                    tls_socket.close();\n                    return ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed;\n                };\n                if (!std.mem.eql(u8, negotiated, \"h2\")) {\n                    tls_socket.close();\n                    return ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed;\n                }\n            }\n\n            break :blk tls_socket;\n        } else blk: {\n            // Plaintext connection\n            break :blk Socket.Plain.init_client(fd);\n        };\n        const tls_end_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n        const tls_handshake_duration_ns = if (upstream.tls)\n            time.elapsedNanos(tls_start_ns, tls_end_ns)\n        else\n            0;\n\n        // Build connection with timestamps\n        const now_ns = time.monotonicNanos();\n        const conn = Connection{\n            .socket = socket,\n            .created_ns = now_ns,\n            .last_used_ns = now_ns,\n        };\n\n        return ConnectResult{\n            .conn = conn,\n            .dns_duration_ns = dns_duration_ns,\n            .tcp_connect_duration_ns = tcp_connect_duration_ns,\n            .tls_handshake_duration_ns = tls_handshake_duration_ns,\n            .local_port = local_port,\n            .connect_timeout_honored = tcp_result.timeout_honored,\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Send an HTTP request on an existing connection.\n    /// Delegates to request.sendRequest with proper error mapping.\n    /// TigerStyle S1: Precondition assertions.\n    pub fn sendRequest(\n        self: *Client,\n        conn: *Connection,\n        req: *const types.Request,\n        effective_path: ?[]const u8,\n    ) ClientError!void {\n        _ = self; // Client state not needed for send\n\n        // S1: preconditions\n        const path = effective_path orelse req.path;\n        assert(path.len > 0); // S1: non-empty path\n\n        request_mod.sendRequest(&conn.socket, req, effective_path) catch |err| {\n            return mapRequestError(err);\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Read HTTP response headers from an existing connection.\n    /// Delegates to response.readResponseHeaders with proper error mapping.\n    /// TigerStyle S1: Precondition assertions.\n    pub fn readResponseHeaders(\n        self: *Client,\n        conn: *Connection,\n        header_buf: []u8,\n    ) ClientError!ResponseHeaders {\n        _ = self; // Client state not needed for receive\n\n        // S1: preconditions\n        assert(header_buf.len > 0); // S1: non-empty buffer\n        assert(header_buf.len <= config.MAX_HEADER_SIZE_BYTES); // S1: bounded buffer\n\n        return response_mod.readResponseHeaders(&conn.socket, header_buf) catch |err| {\n            return mapResponseError(err);\n        };\n    }\n\n    /// Perform a complete HTTP request (connect + send + read headers).\n    /// Convenience function for simple request/response flows.\n    /// TigerStyle S1: Precondition assertions.\n    pub fn request(\n        self: *Client,\n        upstream: Upstream,\n        req: *const types.Request,\n        header_buf: []u8,\n        io: Io,\n    ) ClientError!RequestResult {\n        // S1: preconditions\n        assert(upstream.host.len > 0); // S1: non-empty host\n        assert(header_buf.len > 0); // S1: non-empty buffer\n\n        // Step 1: Connect\n        var connect_result = try self.connect(upstream, io);\n        errdefer connect_result.conn.close();\n\n        // Step 2: Send request\n        try self.sendRequest(&connect_result.conn, req, null);\n\n        // Step 3: Read response headers\n        const response = try self.readResponseHeaders(&connect_result.conn, header_buf);\n\n        // S2: postcondition - valid response status\n        assert(response.status >= 100 and response.status <= 599);\n\n        return .{\n            .conn = connect_result.conn,\n            .response = response,\n        };\n    }\n};\n\n// =============================================================================\n// Internal Functions\n// =============================================================================\n\n/// Get local port from connected socket.\n/// Returns 0 if unable to retrieve (non-fatal).\n/// TigerStyle: Graceful fallback, no panic on failure.\nfn getLocalPort(fd: i32) u16 {\n    assert(fd >= 0);\n\n    var addr: posix.sockaddr.in = std.mem.zeroes(posix.sockaddr.in);\n    var addr_len: posix.socklen_t = @sizeOf(posix.sockaddr.in);\n\n    if (std.c.getsockname(fd, @ptrCast(&addr), &addr_len) != 0) {\n        return 0;\n    }\n\n    return std.mem.bigToNative(u16, addr.port);\n}\n\n/// Perform TCP connection using Io async API.\n/// TigerStyle: Bounded via Io cancellation, explicit error return.\nfn tcpConnect(address: Io.net.IpAddress, io: Io, connect_timeout: Io.Timeout) !TcpConnectResult {\n    // Use IpAddress.connect() to perform async TCP connect\n    // This creates the socket and connects in one step.\n    const stream = address.connect(io, .{\n        .mode = .stream,\n        .timeout = connect_timeout,\n    }) catch |err| {\n        if (err == error.OptionUnsupported and connect_timeout != .none) {\n            // Some IO backends (notably uring today) do not yet support\n            // connect-time timeout options. Fall back to backend-default connect\n            // semantics so callers can still establish connections.\n            const fallback = address.connect(io, .{\n                .mode = .stream,\n                .timeout = .none,\n            }) catch |fallback_err| {\n                return fallback_err;\n            };\n            return .{\n                .fd = fallback.socket.handle,\n                .timeout_honored = false,\n            };\n        }\n        return err;\n    };\n\n    return .{\n        .fd = stream.socket.handle,\n        .timeout_honored = true,\n    };\n}\n\n/// Map TCP connect errors to ClientError.\n/// TigerStyle S6: Explicit error handling.\nfn mapConnectError(err: anyerror) ClientError {\n    return switch (err) {\n        error.ConnectionRefused => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n        error.NetworkUnreachable => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n        error.ConnectionFailed => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n        error.ConnectionTimedOut, error.Timeout => ClientError.TcpConnectTimeout,\n        error.ConnectionResetByPeer => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n        else => ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n    };\n}\n\n/// Map request module errors to ClientError.\n/// TigerStyle S6: Explicit error handling.\nfn mapRequestError(err: request_mod.ClientError) ClientError {\n    return switch (err) {\n        request_mod.ClientError.SendFailed => ClientError.SendFailed,\n        request_mod.ClientError.SendTimeout => ClientError.SendTimeout,\n        request_mod.ClientError.BufferTooSmall => ClientError.BufferTooSmall,\n    };\n}\n\n/// Map response module errors to ClientError.\n/// TigerStyle S6: Explicit error handling.\nfn mapResponseError(err: ResponseError) ClientError {\n    return switch (err) {\n        ResponseError.RecvFailed => ClientError.RecvFailed,\n        ResponseError.RecvTimeout => ClientError.RecvTimeout,\n        ResponseError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge => ClientError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge,\n        ResponseError.InvalidResponseStatus => ClientError.InvalidResponseStatus,\n        ResponseError.InvalidResponseHeaders => ClientError.InvalidResponseHeaders,\n        ResponseError.ConnectionClosed => ClientError.ConnectionClosed,\n    };\n}\n\n// =============================================================================\n// Tests\n// =============================================================================\n\ntest \"Client.init creates client with valid fields\" {\n    var dns_resolver: DnsResolver = undefined;\n    DnsResolver.init(&dns_resolver, .{});\n    const client = Client.init(\n        std.testing.allocator,\n        &dns_resolver,\n        null, // No TLS\n        false,\n    );\n\n    try std.testing.expect(@intFromPtr(client.dns_resolver) != 0);\n    try std.testing.expect(client.client_ctx == null);\n    try std.testing.expect(client.verify_tls == false);\n}\n\ntest \"Client.init with TLS context\" {\n    var dns_resolver: DnsResolver = undefined;\n    DnsResolver.init(&dns_resolver, .{});\n\n    // We can't actually create a valid SSL_CTX in tests without OpenSSL setup,\n    // but we can verify the field is stored correctly with a dummy pointer.\n    // In real usage, the caller provides a properly initialized SSL_CTX.\n    const client = Client.init(\n        std.testing.allocator,\n        &dns_resolver,\n        null, // No TLS in test\n        true, // verify_tls enabled\n    );\n\n    try std.testing.expect(client.verify_tls == true);\n}\n\ntest \"Client.deinit is safe to call\" {\n    var dns_resolver: DnsResolver = undefined;\n    DnsResolver.init(&dns_resolver, .{});\n    var client = Client.init(\n        std.testing.allocator,\n        &dns_resolver,\n        null,\n        false,\n    );\n\n    // Should not crash\n    client.deinit();\n}\n\ntest \"ClientError error set has all expected variants\" {\n    // Verify all error variants exist\n    const errors = [_]ClientError{\n        ClientError.DnsResolutionFailed,\n        ClientError.TcpConnectFailed,\n        ClientError.TcpConnectTimeout,\n        ClientError.TlsHandshakeFailed,\n        ClientError.SendFailed,\n        ClientError.SendTimeout,\n        ClientError.BufferTooSmall,\n        ClientError.RecvFailed,\n        ClientError.RecvTimeout,\n        ClientError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge,\n        ClientError.InvalidResponseStatus,\n        ClientError.InvalidResponseHeaders,\n        ClientError.ConnectionClosed,\n    };\n\n    // Each error should be distinct\n    for (errors, 0..) |err1, i| {\n        for (errors[i + 1 ..]) |err2| {\n            try std.testing.expect(err1 != err2);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\ntest \"RequestResult struct layout\" {\n    // Verify struct has expected fields\n    const info = @typeInfo(RequestResult);\n    try std.testing.expect(info == .@\"struct\");\n\n    const fields = info.@\"struct\".fields;\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(@as(usize, 2), fields.len);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"conn\", fields[0].name);\n    try std.testing.expectEqualStrings(\"response\", fields[1].name);\n}\n\ntest \"mapRequestError maps all variants\" {\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.SendFailed, mapRequestError(request_mod.ClientError.SendFailed));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.SendTimeout, mapRequestError(request_mod.ClientError.SendTimeout));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.BufferTooSmall, mapRequestError(request_mod.ClientError.BufferTooSmall));\n}\n\ntest \"mapResponseError maps all variants\" {\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.RecvFailed, mapResponseError(ResponseError.RecvFailed));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.RecvTimeout, mapResponseError(ResponseError.RecvTimeout));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge, mapResponseError(ResponseError.ResponseHeadersTooLarge));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.InvalidResponseStatus, mapResponseError(ResponseError.InvalidResponseStatus));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.InvalidResponseHeaders, mapResponseError(ResponseError.InvalidResponseHeaders));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.ConnectionClosed, mapResponseError(ResponseError.ConnectionClosed));\n}\n\ntest \"mapConnectError maps common errors\" {\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.ConnectionRefused));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.NetworkUnreachable));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.ConnectionFailed));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectTimeout, mapConnectError(error.ConnectionTimedOut));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectTimeout, mapConnectError(error.Timeout));\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.ConnectionResetByPeer));\n    // Unknown errors map to TcpConnectFailed\n    try std.testing.expectEqual(ClientError.TcpConnectFailed, mapConnectError(error.OutOfMemory));\n}\n","numLines":595,"startLine":1,"totalLines":595}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ee312d6b-4c6f-4bb9-aa92-0c94fd1af991","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/nick/repos/serval","sessionId":"646a4f49-bebb-4328-acf0-8f573ea592f5","version":"2.1.86","gitBranch":"main","slug":"graceful-swimming-stream"}
