{"parentUuid":"559ad12c-197e-4769-9a2d-316c37b388af","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BuQ3oA2BZuipDCaH7qmWhj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YMmbYyLMkEqfDA3fz65xZ3","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/nick/.claude/projects/-home-nick-repos-serval/memory/project_serval.md","content":"---\nname: serval project context\ndescription: Zig-based HTTP reverse proxy / load balancer — build system, test commands, module layout, coding conventions\ntype: project\n---\n\nServal is a Zig HTTP reverse proxy and load balancer with modules: serval-core, serval-lb, serval-health, serval-prober, serval-client, serval-router, serval-tls, serval-net, serval-pool, serval-server, serval-socket, serval-waf, etc.\n\n**Build/test:** `zig build test` (all), `zig build test-lb`, `zig build test-health`, etc. Zig 0.16-dev.\n\n**Coding style:** TigerStyle — ~2 assertions per function, no allocation after init, bounded loops, explicit types, cache-line alignment where needed. Out-pointer init (C3) for large structs.\n\n**How to apply:** Follow TigerStyle assert patterns, use `zig build test-<module>` for focused testing, check `build.zig` for available test steps.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":293,"cache_read_input_tokens":69662,"output_tokens":469,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":293,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZXj2LcneharNYxdZ8B4a","type":"assistant","uuid":"26af8810-6c05-4b47-b814-3f5e18633b28","timestamp":"2026-03-29T16:57:45.324Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/nick/repos/serval","sessionId":"646a4f49-bebb-4328-acf0-8f573ea592f5","version":"2.1.86","gitBranch":"main","slug":"graceful-swimmin