{"parentUuid":"27ddf23b-e568-4949-abff-a245b02f6223","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"cb36699f-289e-491d-a266-071c1e013776","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"• 1. High: Verification commands can mask test failures\n      - Multiple steps use pipelines like zig build ... 2>&1 | tail -20 and ... | grep ... (docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:83, docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:223,\n        docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:304, docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:388, docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:505).\n      - Without set -o pipefail, pipeline exit status is from tail/grep, not zig build. This is not enterprise-safe verification.\n  2. Medium: Single global mutex in HealthState is a potential hot-path bottleneck\n      - Plan introduces one counter_mutex protecting all counter updates (docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:95, docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:130, docs/plans/2026-03-29-\n        lb-health-findings-fixes.md:152).\n      - Correctness improves, but this serializes all passive/prober updates across all backends. For high-throughput LB, that may regress performance and tail latency.\n  3. Medium: Shutdown-latency test does not validate the new interruptible sleep behavior\n      - Proposed test only covers probe_running = false at entry (docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:349, docs/plans/2026-03-29-lb-health-findings-fixes.md:352).\n      - It does not exercise the key path where the loop is sleeping and the flag flips to false mid-interval.\n\n  Overall: plan is much better now and mostly implementable; the main blocker is verification rigor (pipeline masking), plus two residual performance/test-depth risks."},"uuid":"60de2848-4337-4253-ad7a-1ab2d6a111fc","timestamp":"2026-03-29T17:38:45.802Z","permissionMode":"acceptEdits","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/home/nick/repos/serval","sessionId":"646